					<head>Commentary</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597" rend="visible">
						<summary>The commentary of Japheth ben Ali ha-Levi on the book of Job, chapters 1-22.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he" otherLangs="jrb">Hebrew, Judeo-Arabic</textLang>
						<msItem n="0" rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597">
							<locus from="1r" to="127v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Perush Iyov</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">פרוש איוב</title>
							<author key="http://viaf.org/viaf/54984961">
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/54984961" xml:lang="en">Japheth ben Ali, ha-Levi,‏ active 10th century </persName>
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/54984961" xml:lang="he">יפת בן עלי, הלוי</persName>
							</author>
							<note>
								<p>The pointed Hebrew text, accompanied by a verse by verse Arabic translation, is embodied.</p>
								<p>Of the Hebrew text the following parts are preserved: 1:2-12, 1:16-2:10, 2:12, 3:10-17, 3:23-4:7, 4:12-14, 5:4-12, 5:24, 6:27-7:3, 7:17-20, 8:7-9:4, 9:12 (in part)-19, 22-23, 31-32, 10:2-22, 11:15-12:3, 12:9-14:3, 14:22, 15:5-14 (in part), 17-28, 15:33-16:2, 16:7-17:9, 17:12-19:4, 19:6-20:9, 21:14-22:29.</p>
								<p>Has a scribal subscription at the beginning.</p>
								<p>Masoretic division into sections and קרי are marked in the margins.</p>
								<p>The preserved text is divided into 7 sections, beginnings of which are marked in the margins of folios 25v, 44v, 59v, 81v, 98v, 107r, 117v.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the 15th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
